WEBVTT

00:06.073 --> 00:07.608
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:07.641 --> 00:12.112
GUILLERMO GARCIA GOMEZ.
THERE'S A TUNNEL.

00:12.145 --> 00:14.314
YOU MAKE A BUST,
YOU GET GUILLERMO,

00:14.348 --> 00:16.016
AND IT NEVER
COMES BACK TO ME.

00:16.049 --> 00:18.652
WHY ARE WE FOCUSING
ON MY CREW?

00:18.685 --> 00:20.120
MY PEOPLE DON'T TALK.

00:20.153 --> 00:22.256
WHEN DID WE DECIDE YOU
WERE GONNA MOVE YOUR PLANTS?

00:22.289 --> 00:24.791
SOMETHING KIND OF
FELL INTO MY LAP.

00:24.825 --> 00:26.860
WHERE EXACTLY
IS THIS GROW ROOM?

00:26.894 --> 00:28.195
BACK OF A CHEESE SHOP.

00:28.228 --> 00:29.530
I COULD GET SOME POT.

00:29.563 --> 00:31.565
YOU TOTALLY ROCK.

00:31.598 --> 00:32.733
MARIA AND I HAD SEX.

00:32.766 --> 00:34.334
WHAT?
I LOVE HIM.

00:34.368 --> 00:36.036
DEPARTMENT OF IMMIGRATION
AND NATURALIZATION.

00:36.069 --> 00:37.804
WE HAPPEN TO HAVE A DAUGHTER
OUT THERE

00:37.838 --> 00:39.773
WHO HASN'T SEEN YOU
IN OVER TWO YEARS.

00:39.806 --> 00:41.441
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE QUINN IS.

00:41.475 --> 00:43.777
SHE'S LIVING IN OAXACA
WITH A GUY NAMED RODOLFO.

00:43.810 --> 00:45.045
WHO ARE THE GIRLS?

00:45.078 --> 00:47.281
MY DAUGHTERS.

00:47.314 --> 00:49.149
WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO NOW?

00:49.183 --> 00:51.351
WE'LL ARREST YOU TOMORROW,
MAKE IT LOOK RIGHT.

00:51.385 --> 00:55.289
WE'LL PRETEND TO ASK, AND
YOU'LL PRETEND TO KNOW NOTHING.

00:55.322 --> 00:56.890
IF YOU DON'T
HAVE ANY PLANS...

00:56.924 --> 01:00.227
I'M SEEING SOMEONE.
AGENT SHLATTER.

01:00.260 --> 01:03.397
Cesar:
WHO IS THE INFORMANT?

01:03.430 --> 01:06.433
NANCY BOTWIN.

01:07.835 --> 01:11.038
‐‐ Captions by VITAC ‐‐
www.vitac.com

01:56.583 --> 01:59.286
Sí, SEÑOR.

02:05.025 --> 02:07.528
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

02:09.329 --> 02:12.299
MY CLIENT
RESERVES THE RIGHT ‐‐
SHUT THE FUCK UP.

02:12.332 --> 02:16.270
SO, YOU HAD NO IDEA THAT THERE
WAS A TUNNEL IN THE BACK ROOM

02:16.303 --> 02:18.672
THAT WAS BEING USED
TO TRANSPORT NARCOTICS

02:18.705 --> 02:21.008
FROM MEXICO
TO THE UNITED STATES?

02:21.041 --> 02:22.242
THEY KEPT THE ROOM LOCKED.

02:22.276 --> 02:24.578
AND IT DIDN'T STRIKE YOU
AS ODD THAT STRANGE MEN

02:24.611 --> 02:27.414
WERE SHUTTLING PACKAGES
OUT OF THERE ALL DAY LONG?

02:27.447 --> 02:30.851
OF COURSE IT STRUCK ME AS ODD,
BUT I DIDN'T ASK ANY QUESTIONS

02:30.884 --> 02:32.419
BECAUSE A PAYCHECK
IS A PAYCHECK.

02:32.452 --> 02:35.789
THERE IS NO LAW AGAINST BEING
THE UNWITTING PARTICIPANT

02:35.822 --> 02:38.859
IN A CRIME IF THERE IS NO
PRIOR KNOWLEDGE OF SAID CRIME.

02:38.892 --> 02:43.630
THANK YOU
FOR THAT FASCINATING TIDBIT.

02:43.664 --> 02:45.332
[ DOOR OPENS ]

02:47.201 --> 02:49.369
[ WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY ]

02:56.643 --> 02:58.378
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

02:58.412 --> 03:04.518
YOU KNOW, I DON'T ACTUALLY
TURN 18 UNTIL 10:47,

03:04.551 --> 03:07.120
SO WE GOT ANOTHER 15 MINUTES
TO BREAK THE LAW.

03:07.154 --> 03:10.190
WE REALLY SHOULDN'T BE
WASTING IT BY TALKING.

03:12.025 --> 03:13.994
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:14.027 --> 03:15.996
WHO'S THAT?

03:16.029 --> 03:18.232
DAMN IT!
HE SAID NOON!

03:18.265 --> 03:20.000
WHO SAID NOON?
JUST GET DRESSED.

03:20.033 --> 03:22.169
HEY, GUYS.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.337
Henry: OH, THIS IS NICE.
VERY NICE.

03:23.370 --> 03:25.339
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

03:25.372 --> 03:27.341
RAD TOLD ME
IT WAS A SPECIAL OCCASION.

03:27.374 --> 03:28.742
YOUR BOYFRIEND'S
18th BIRTHDAY?

03:28.775 --> 03:30.210
RAD, I WANT YOU
TO LEAVE THE ROOM

03:30.244 --> 03:32.045
AND SHUT THE DOOR
BEHIND YOU, OKAY?

03:32.079 --> 03:33.180
HEY, TWINKIE. SMILE.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.381
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

03:34.414 --> 03:36.316
FAMILY‐COURT JUDGE
IS GONNA LOVE THIS.

03:36.350 --> 03:39.219
SOLE CUSTODY IS THE ONLY THING
THAT MAKES SENSE, HENRY.

03:39.253 --> 03:40.988
RAD SHOULDN'T HAVE TO SHUTTLE
BACK AND FORTH TO NAPA

03:41.021 --> 03:43.690
JUST BECAUSE YOU FELL IN
LOVE WITH SOME TASTING‐ROOM
TRAMP FROM TREFETHEN.

03:43.724 --> 03:46.026
YEAH, I STILL LOVE MY KID.
THEN LIVE NEAR HIM.

03:46.059 --> 03:48.262
YOU TOOK THE CHEESE STORE.
YOU TOOK THIS HOUSE.

03:48.295 --> 03:49.830
YOU'RE NOT TAKING MY SON.

03:49.863 --> 03:51.298
YOU LEFT US.
I LEFT <i>YOU.</i>

03:51.331 --> 03:53.300
I WANT TO MAKE SURE SOMEONE'S
LOOKING AFTER MY SON

03:53.333 --> 03:55.169
WHILE YOU'RE GETTING HIGH
AND BANGING 'NSYNC.

03:55.202 --> 03:57.304
FUNNY, BECAUSE YOU WERE
NEVER REALLY THAT CONCERNED

03:57.337 --> 03:58.372
ABOUT RAD
WHILE YOU WERE CHEATING.

03:58.405 --> 03:59.706
WELL, MAYBE
I WOULDN'T HAVE CHEATED

03:59.740 --> 04:01.408
IF YOU WEREN'T
SUCH A FUCKING BITCH.

04:01.441 --> 04:03.911
THAT'S GREAT. BLAME ME.
SORRY, DUDE.

04:03.944 --> 04:07.247
YEAH. YOU LEAVING?

04:07.281 --> 04:08.882
I WANT YOU OUT OF HERE
RIGHT NOW.

04:08.916 --> 04:11.785
YEAH.

04:11.818 --> 04:15.455
YEAH.

04:15.489 --> 04:16.423
Henry: FUCK YOU.

04:21.795 --> 04:24.498
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

04:30.671 --> 04:31.972
GET OUT.

04:32.005 --> 04:33.507
WELL,
I'M HER LEGAL REPRE‐‐

04:33.540 --> 04:35.909
GET OUT, OR I'LL FUCKING
THROW YOU THROUGH THE WINDOW.

04:35.943 --> 04:38.345
OH, I‐IT'S OKAY,
DEAN. GO.

04:38.378 --> 04:40.881
NO, IT IS DEFINITELY NOT OKAY.
I'M HER ‐‐

04:40.914 --> 04:42.049
AAH! OKA‐‐

04:42.082 --> 04:44.585
THIS IS A FLAGRANT MISCARRIAGE
OF JUSTICE!

04:51.024 --> 04:55.495
MY PARTNER IS DEAD.

04:55.529 --> 04:57.631
OH, MY GOD.

04:57.664 --> 05:00.834
HIS BODY WAS FOUND HANGING
ON THE BORDER FENCE.

05:00.868 --> 05:03.504
HE DIDN'T
HAVE A FUCKING FACE.

05:03.537 --> 05:06.640
NO FACE?

05:10.177 --> 05:13.046
WHO OWNS THE TUNNEL?

05:14.314 --> 05:17.484
WHO OWNS
THE FUCKING TUNNEL?!

05:17.518 --> 05:18.986
YOU TELL ME NOW!

05:19.019 --> 05:20.521
I‐I DON'T KNOW.

05:20.554 --> 05:21.688
BULLSHIT!

05:23.590 --> 05:25.125
WHO'S GUILLERMO'S BOSS?

05:26.326 --> 05:29.830
WHO'S THE FUCKING ANIMAL
ON THE OTHER SIDE OF THE FENCE?

05:29.863 --> 05:32.499
I‐I WASN'T ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE FENCE.

05:32.533 --> 05:33.967
I WAS ON THIS SIDE.

05:37.237 --> 05:42.743
I'M GONNA GET THIS GUY,
WITH OR WITHOUT YOU.

05:42.776 --> 05:45.879
AND I'M GONNA KILL HIM...

05:45.913 --> 05:50.517
AFTER I KILL
EVERYONE HE LOVES.

05:50.551 --> 05:53.453
AND I'M GONNA DO IT ALONE.

05:55.822 --> 05:59.293
AND IF I FIND OUT...

05:59.326 --> 06:01.895
YOU MADE ME
GO THE LONG WAY,

06:01.929 --> 06:06.099
I'M GONNA KILL YOU, TOO.

06:10.037 --> 06:14.274
HE WAS MY PARTNER.

06:17.511 --> 06:21.114
[ HORN HONKING,
CHICKENS SQUAWKING ]

06:25.485 --> 06:28.088
Celia: NO BUSO DIRECTO.

06:28.121 --> 06:31.892
HOW MUCHAS TICKETS
DO I NEED?

06:31.925 --> 06:35.162
FIRST TO SAN NICOLáS.
THEN TO SAN CRISTOBAL.

06:35.195 --> 06:37.731
THAT CHICKEN
JUST SNEEZED ON ME.

06:37.764 --> 06:39.233
THEN TO MIXTEPEC.

06:39.266 --> 06:43.704
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT ABOUT SITIO DE PERDIDO?

06:43.737 --> 06:47.207
THAT'S WHERE I NEED TO GO.
THAT'S WHERE MY DAUGHTER IS.

06:47.241 --> 06:51.345
GIVE THEM
TO YOUR DAUGHTER.

06:54.214 --> 06:57.317
BEAUTIFUL MOVIE STAR?

06:57.351 --> 07:00.420
KATHLEEN TURNER.
"BODY HEAT." IS IT YOU?

07:00.454 --> 07:03.557
OF COURSE IT'S ME.

07:03.590 --> 07:06.960
BUT DON'T TELL ANYONE.
I'M RESEARCHING A FILM.

07:06.994 --> 07:09.963
YOU KNOW, DONKEY HERE
WAS AN ACTOR IN LIVE SHOW.

07:09.997 --> 07:11.298
OH, YOU DON'T SAY.

07:11.331 --> 07:12.466
NO, I SAY.

07:12.499 --> 07:14.568
THEN HE GOT REPLACED
BY A YOUNGER DONKEY

07:14.601 --> 07:19.439
BECAUSE HIS COJONES ‐‐
THEY GROW MUY DROOPY.

07:19.473 --> 07:22.609
AH. TIME IS CRUEL.

07:27.481 --> 07:28.649
Quinn: HEY, MOM.

07:34.054 --> 07:35.389
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

07:40.527 --> 07:43.163
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO
HAVE HER DEPORTED.

07:43.197 --> 07:46.166
OH, BUT YOU
HAD TO SCREW HER, RIGHT?

07:46.200 --> 07:49.069
YEAH, SHE'S HOT.
BUT THE I. N. S.?

07:49.102 --> 07:51.371
SHE WOULDN'T FUCK ME.
BUT SHE FUCKED YOU.

07:51.405 --> 07:54.308
HUH, WELL, FUCK HER ‐‐
AND FUCK YOU!

07:54.341 --> 07:57.211
THAT WAS REALLY AWFUL, DOUG...
EVEN FOR YOU.

07:57.244 --> 08:00.247
THERE ARE RULES AMONG MEN,
ANDY. CODES.

08:00.280 --> 08:02.749
YOU DON'T HAVE SEX
WITH YOUR FRIEND'S GIRL...EVER!

08:02.783 --> 08:03.951
CODE BREAKER!

08:03.984 --> 08:06.987
YOU HAD SEX WITH CELIA,
YOUR FRIEND DEAN'S WIFE!

08:07.020 --> 08:09.623
SO, WHO'S THE ORIGINAL
CODE BREAKER, CODE BREAKER?

08:11.191 --> 08:13.694
ME.
I'M A CODE BREAKER.

08:13.727 --> 08:16.196
ME, TOO. ME, TOO.
SORRY, MAN.

08:16.230 --> 08:17.531
YEAH, I'M SORRY, TOO.
I'M SORRY.

08:20.467 --> 08:22.035
I REALLY LIKED HER.

08:22.069 --> 08:25.405
NO, YOU DIDN'T REALLY
"LIKE HER" LIKE HER.

08:25.439 --> 08:27.074
SHE WAS A FANTASY.

08:27.107 --> 08:29.076
YOU'RE STILL TOO IN LOVE
WITH DANA TO "LIKE" LIKE ANYONE.

08:29.109 --> 08:32.145
WELL, YOU'RE IN LOVE
WITH NANCY.

08:34.248 --> 08:36.416
I'M NOT IN LOVE WITH NANCY.

08:36.450 --> 08:37.417
YOU SO ARE.

08:37.451 --> 08:39.720
WHY ELSE WOULD YOU PUT UP
WITH ALL HER CRAP?

08:39.753 --> 08:41.421
I ‐‐

08:43.524 --> 08:44.625
THE KIDS.

08:44.658 --> 08:46.627
[ SCOFFS ]

08:46.660 --> 08:48.795
MY BROTHER.

08:48.829 --> 08:51.031
NANCY.

08:53.901 --> 08:55.736
I DON'T LOVE NANCY,
OKAY? SHUT UP.

08:55.769 --> 08:57.137
YOU SHUT UP.
SO, YOU SHUT UP.

08:57.171 --> 08:59.373
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]
OH. HOLD THAT THOUGHT.

08:59.406 --> 09:03.777
OH, HI, SILAS,
SON OF MY DEAD BROTHER.

09:03.810 --> 09:05.379
OH.

09:05.412 --> 09:06.880
WHERE?

09:06.914 --> 09:09.816
OKAY. OKAY.
YEAH, I'LL SEE YOU SOON.

09:09.850 --> 09:11.251
I GOT TO GO.

09:11.285 --> 09:12.252
YOU WANT TO
SMOKE OUT FIRST?

09:12.286 --> 09:14.421
I CAN'T.
SHIT'S BLOWING UP.

09:14.454 --> 09:17.624
HOW COME YOU ALWAYS HAVE
SHIT BLOWING UP?

09:17.658 --> 09:18.725
WHERE'S MY SHIT?

09:18.759 --> 09:20.827
I USED TO HAVE SHIT.
IT USED TO BLOW UP ALL THE TIME.

09:20.861 --> 09:22.629
NOW NOTHING.
SHIT JUST SITS THERE.

09:22.663 --> 09:24.831
THAT'S SOME TOUGH SHIT.

09:24.865 --> 09:26.200
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:26.233 --> 09:28.468
SHIT.

09:30.470 --> 09:31.939
[ PIANO PLAYING ]

09:31.972 --> 09:34.174
[ CLANGING ]

09:37.511 --> 09:39.112
SURE IT WON'T GET TOWED?

09:39.146 --> 09:41.348
IT'S A SECURE LOT.
IT'LL BE FINE FOR A NIGHT.

09:41.381 --> 09:42.983
PUT THE SANDWICHES
IN THE FREEZER.

09:43.016 --> 09:45.352
AND THEN AS SOON
AS I REACH DOUG,

09:45.385 --> 09:47.654
WE'LL MOVE IT ALL
TO HIS HOUSE.

09:47.688 --> 09:49.489
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, SILAS.

09:49.523 --> 09:51.792
Andy: HOLY SHIT.

09:51.825 --> 09:55.529
THAT'S RIGHT.
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

09:55.562 --> 09:58.732
I'M SUCH A PHASEHEAD.
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY ANYTHING?

09:58.765 --> 10:00.067
18, RIGHT?

10:00.100 --> 10:01.101
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

10:01.134 --> 10:02.503
SURE, IT'S A BIG DEAL.

10:02.536 --> 10:04.705
COULD YOU STOP PLAYING
THAT FUCKING PIANO?!

10:04.738 --> 10:05.739
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

10:10.744 --> 10:13.447
WOW.
LOOK WHO'S NOT IN JAIL.

10:13.480 --> 10:14.615
TOLD YOU I'D BE BACK.

10:14.648 --> 10:15.649
WHAT HAPPENED?

10:15.682 --> 10:16.550
NOTHING.

10:16.583 --> 10:21.188
ASKED ME A FEW QUESTIONS.
SENT ME HOME.

10:21.221 --> 10:22.923
I'M JUST A SALESGIRL.

10:22.956 --> 10:24.491
SURE YOU ARE.

10:24.525 --> 10:26.193
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, SILAS.

10:26.226 --> 10:29.696
HAVE A GOOD TIME
WITH LISA TONIGHT.

10:29.730 --> 10:31.565
DINNER'S OFF.
WE'RE OFF.

10:31.598 --> 10:33.634
HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO ME.

10:33.667 --> 10:37.037
WHAT? OH.

10:37.070 --> 10:40.073
UH...WELL, WHY DON'T
WE ALL GO OUT, THEN?

10:40.107 --> 10:43.810
HOW ABOUT THAT ITALIAN PLACE
ON OCEAN, SAY 7:00?

10:43.844 --> 10:47.514
OKAY?
I'M GONNA GO TAKE A BATH.

10:47.548 --> 10:48.549
MOM...

10:48.582 --> 10:50.784
REMEMBER THAT SMALL‐BUSINESS
LOAN WE DISCUSSED?

10:50.817 --> 10:53.754
IT WOULD BE
A GREAT BIRTHDAY GIFT.

10:53.787 --> 10:55.255
SILAS...

10:55.289 --> 10:57.090
ARE YOU GONNA BACK ME
OR NOT?

10:57.124 --> 10:58.892
UH, THIS IS A BAD TIME.

10:58.926 --> 11:00.127
AND?

11:00.160 --> 11:02.629
AND IT'S A BAD TIME.

11:02.663 --> 11:04.831
YEAH. WELL...

11:04.865 --> 11:07.801
THANKS FOR GIVING IT
SOME THOUGHT.

11:07.835 --> 11:10.037
[ SIGHS ]

11:15.709 --> 11:17.344
HI, IT'S ME.

11:17.377 --> 11:18.645
Esteban: Hey.

11:18.679 --> 11:20.214
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

11:20.247 --> 11:21.515
OKAY.

11:21.548 --> 11:26.320
I GOT TAKEN INTO CUSTODY,
QUESTIONED, RELEASED.

11:26.353 --> 11:28.188
And?

11:28.222 --> 11:31.258
UH, HAD PANCAKES
FOR BREAKFAST.

11:31.291 --> 11:34.394
HMM. REALLY?
WHAT KIND?

11:36.563 --> 11:38.999
BLUEBERRY.

11:39.032 --> 11:41.502
WHAT DID YOU HAVE
FOR BREAKFAST?

11:41.535 --> 11:43.136
YOGURT...

11:43.170 --> 11:44.872
AND COFFEE AND TOAST.

11:44.905 --> 11:49.476
SOUNDS LIKE
A NICE BREAKFAST.

11:49.510 --> 11:52.613
I'D LIKE TO SEE YOU.

11:54.748 --> 11:56.550
I'D LIKE TO SEE YOU, TOO.

11:56.583 --> 11:58.051
TONIGHT.

11:59.419 --> 12:00.888
TONIGHT?

12:00.921 --> 12:03.423
I WILL SEND A CAR.

12:03.457 --> 12:05.626
HAS TO BE TONIGHT?

12:05.659 --> 12:08.262
YES.

12:11.198 --> 12:13.534
I CAN DRIVE MYSELF.

12:13.567 --> 12:15.869
YOU WILL COME.

12:15.903 --> 12:18.105
I SAID I WOULD.

12:20.507 --> 12:22.543
TE AMO.

12:24.578 --> 12:26.413
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

12:26.446 --> 12:27.514
YO TAMBIéN.

12:48.902 --> 12:51.371
[ DOOR OPENS ]

12:51.405 --> 12:52.539
[ KNOCKING ]

12:52.573 --> 12:54.741
Andy: NANCY?

12:54.775 --> 12:57.177
GO AWAY, ANDY.

12:57.211 --> 13:00.113
NANCY, CAN I COME IN?

13:00.147 --> 13:02.349
NO.

13:02.382 --> 13:04.451
I'M COMING IN.

13:16.496 --> 13:19.032
COULD YOU CLOSE THE DOOR
BEHIND YOU?

13:19.066 --> 13:20.968
I CAN SEE YOUR BOOBIES.

13:21.001 --> 13:23.136
GOOD FOR YOU.

13:23.170 --> 13:26.607
CLOSE THE DOOR
AND SIT DOWN.

13:37.518 --> 13:39.186
THEY'RE NICE.

13:41.188 --> 13:42.923
BIGGER THAN I THOUGHT.

13:42.956 --> 13:45.926
THANKS.

13:45.959 --> 13:48.762
YOU WANT A TOWEL
OR SOMETHING?

13:48.795 --> 13:50.097
TWO WASHCLOTHS?

13:50.130 --> 13:51.865
ANDY.
FINE. FINE.

13:51.899 --> 13:54.034
ARE YOU GOING TO JAIL?

13:54.067 --> 13:57.137
NO.
I'M NOT GOING TO JAIL.

13:57.171 --> 13:58.939
WHY NOT?
WHY AREN'T YOU GOING TO JAIL?

13:58.972 --> 14:01.842
I CAN'T TELL YOU.

14:01.875 --> 14:02.976
YOU HAVE TO TELL ME.

14:03.010 --> 14:04.611
I CAN'T.
I CAN'T TELL ANYONE.

14:09.483 --> 14:10.350
[ SIGHS ]

14:10.384 --> 14:13.887
COULD YOU TURN ON THE WATER
FOR ME...

14:13.921 --> 14:15.656
ADD SOME BUBBLES?

14:15.689 --> 14:17.558
YEAH, SURE.

14:30.370 --> 14:35.375
I USED TO BE ABLE TO RATIONALIZE
THE THINGS I DID, ANDY.

14:35.409 --> 14:38.145
YEAH.

14:38.178 --> 14:41.648
YOU WERE GOOD AT THAT.

14:41.682 --> 14:43.483
NOT ANYMORE.

14:43.517 --> 14:45.185
AT SOME POINT RECENTLY,

14:45.219 --> 14:47.354
EVERYTHING
BECAME RIGHT OR WRONG.

14:47.387 --> 14:49.523
RIGHT OR WRONG.

14:51.058 --> 14:53.327
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

14:57.497 --> 15:00.267
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

15:05.539 --> 15:08.742
WHAT DID YOU DO?

15:08.775 --> 15:11.578
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

15:11.612 --> 15:13.614
[ SIGHS ]

15:16.116 --> 15:21.321
THERE WAS THIS GIRL...
IN A BLUE DRESS.

15:23.190 --> 15:25.225
SHE WAS SO YOUNG.

15:25.259 --> 15:29.196
SHE HAD THIS BAG
WITH A BUTTERFLY ON IT.

15:29.229 --> 15:32.432
SHE KEPT LOOKING AT ME.

16:28.155 --> 16:29.756
Doug: "DEAR DANA...

16:29.790 --> 16:33.093
"I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW DIFFERENT
REN MAR IS THAN AGRESTIC,

16:33.126 --> 16:36.797
"HOW FAST THINGS MOVE
DOWN BY THE OCEAN.

16:36.830 --> 16:39.032
"I SAW A SURFER ONCE
WHEN I WAS A KID,

16:39.066 --> 16:41.935
"BUT NOW THEY'RE EVERYWHERE.

16:41.969 --> 16:46.273
"BEACH WENT AND GOT ITSELF
IN A BIG DAMN HURRY.

16:46.306 --> 16:49.543
"FOUND MYSELF A CRAPPY STUDIO
APARTMENT OFF THE BOARDWALK.

16:49.576 --> 16:54.748
"IT'S NOTHING FANCY,
BUT IT DOES THE JOB.

16:54.781 --> 16:57.050
"I HAVE TROUBLE SLEEPING.

16:57.084 --> 16:58.485
"THE BED'S TOO SHORT.

16:58.519 --> 17:00.487
"I HAVE BAD DREAMS
LIKE I'M FALLING

17:00.521 --> 17:04.758
"OR I LIVE IN AFRICA
WITH THE MONKEYS.

17:04.791 --> 17:07.194
"I WAKE UP SCARED.

17:07.227 --> 17:11.431
"SOMETIMES IT TAKES ME A WHILE
TO REMEMBER WHERE I AM.

17:11.465 --> 17:13.800
"SINCE LOSING YOU,

17:13.834 --> 17:17.337
I'VE LOST ALL SENSE OF JOY
AND PLEASURE."

17:26.180 --> 17:29.082
"ONLY ONE THING LEFT TO DO."

17:42.996 --> 17:45.499
[ GRUNTING ]

17:48.101 --> 17:50.571
OH, YEAH.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

17:50.604 --> 17:51.738
OH.

17:51.772 --> 17:53.574
OH, GOD.
[ GRUNTS ]

17:53.607 --> 17:55.442
[ MOANS ]

17:55.475 --> 17:56.443
LEGENDARY!

17:56.476 --> 17:58.712
OH!

17:58.745 --> 18:01.248
OOH.

18:01.281 --> 18:05.319
"SO FUCK YOU AND YOUR LAWYERS.
COME GET ME IF YOU WANT.

18:05.352 --> 18:07.654
"I DON'T GIVE A SHIT,
BECAUSE I'M BROKE.

18:07.688 --> 18:10.891
AND WHEN YOU GOT NOTHING,
YOU GOT NOTHING TO LOSE."

18:10.924 --> 18:12.159
[ Sighing ] OOH.

18:12.192 --> 18:14.962
"TAKE CARE. DOUG."

18:14.995 --> 18:18.632
THANK YOU, RODRIGO.

18:18.665 --> 18:20.601
RODOLFO.

18:24.705 --> 18:28.008
HE SEEMS VERY NICE.

18:28.041 --> 18:29.610
HOW DID YOU TWO MEET?

18:29.643 --> 18:34.147
HE TAUGHT AT CASA REFORMA.
POLITICAL SCIENCE.

18:34.181 --> 18:36.149
NOW HE'S WORKING
ON HIS DISSERTATION.

18:36.183 --> 18:38.252
THIS IS GOOD.
WHAT IS IT?

18:38.285 --> 18:41.622
IT'S A SECRET RECIPE
FROM MY MOTHER.

18:41.655 --> 18:42.723
[ THUD ]

18:44.258 --> 18:46.226
HOW LONG
HAVE YOU BEEN SOBER, MOM?

18:46.260 --> 18:47.694
17 DAYS.

18:47.728 --> 18:49.763
GOOD FOR YOU.

18:49.796 --> 18:51.398
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

18:51.431 --> 18:55.302
I AM WORKING MY STEPS,
MAKING AMENDS.

18:55.335 --> 18:57.804
I CAME HERE
TO SAY I'M SORRY.

18:57.838 --> 19:01.608
VERY,
VERY, VERY SORRY.

19:01.642 --> 19:05.546
REALLY AND TRULY SORRY.

19:05.579 --> 19:08.215
SO SORRY.

19:08.248 --> 19:10.050
SHOULD I GET MORE SPECIFIC?

19:10.083 --> 19:12.219
I THINK
WE'RE WAY PAST THAT, MOM.

19:12.252 --> 19:15.556
YOU KNOW, CASA REFORMA WAS
ACTUALLY REALLY GOOD FOR ME.

19:15.589 --> 19:20.761
I MET THIS MAN I LOVE,
AND WE JUST...LIVE.

19:20.794 --> 19:23.597
HUMBLY, SIMPLY.

19:23.630 --> 19:25.699
MY LIFE HAS PURPOSE.

19:25.732 --> 19:27.334
IT'S VERY HOT.
ARE YOU HOT?

19:27.367 --> 19:29.937
AND I'M JUST SO GLAD
THAT YOU CAME HERE TO SEE ME

19:29.970 --> 19:32.673
SO THAT
I COULD TELL YOU THAT

19:32.706 --> 19:35.209
AND TIE YOU UP AND LOCK YOU
IN A ROOM AND KEEP YOU THERE

19:35.242 --> 19:39.246
UNTIL I SELL YOUR ASS
BACK INTO SUBURBAN SLAVERY...

19:40.614 --> 19:42.382
...YOU FUCKING BITCH.

19:42.416 --> 19:45.385
FUCKING...

19:49.223 --> 19:51.191
SHALL I CALL
YOUR FATHER NOW?
YES.

19:51.225 --> 19:54.294
TELL DADDY DEAN
I WANT $200,000,

19:54.328 --> 19:56.330
AND TELL HIM TO BE QUICK
WITH THE CASH.

19:56.363 --> 20:00.100
OR WE'RE GONNA START
SENDING HIM BODY PARTS.

20:00.133 --> 20:02.436
REVOLUTION
IS A VERY SAD AFFAIR.

20:02.469 --> 20:05.506
BUT THESE TEARS ARE SHED
IN THE NAME OF GREATER GOOD.

20:05.539 --> 20:06.406
YEAH?

20:06.440 --> 20:08.642
WELL, FUCK YOU
AND YOUR FAGGY REVOLUTION.

20:08.675 --> 20:11.645
I'M TAKING MY MONEY,
AND I'M MOVING TO BELIZE.

20:14.314 --> 20:16.617
Nancy:
UH, SAN DIEGO, CALIFORNIA.

20:16.650 --> 20:20.587
I NEED THE NUMBER OF, UM,
A GIFT STORE...

20:20.621 --> 20:21.755
PLACE.

20:21.788 --> 20:23.223
GIFT SOMETHING.

20:23.257 --> 20:25.859
Woman: I have nothing listing
for "gift store" in San Diego.

20:25.893 --> 20:27.261
Do you have an address?

20:27.294 --> 20:30.364
I DON'T HAVE AN ADDRESS.
I JUST NEED TO GET A GIFT.

20:30.397 --> 20:33.267
IF YOU TYPE IN "GIFT,"
WHAT COMES UP?

20:33.300 --> 20:35.269
I need the name
of a listing.

20:35.302 --> 20:39.273
UH, PLEASE,
ANYTHING GIFT.

20:39.306 --> 20:41.141
Terrifically
Gift Baskets?

20:41.175 --> 20:43.010
OH, DO THEY DELIVER?

20:43.043 --> 20:46.647
I have no idea, ma'am.
Connecting your call.

20:46.680 --> 20:48.448
[ Ringing ]

20:48.482 --> 20:51.585
Carol: Terrifically
Gift Baskets. This is Carol.

20:51.618 --> 20:52.653
HI, CAROL.

20:52.686 --> 20:56.390
I NEED TO GET A BIRTHDAY GIFT
FOR MY 18‐YEAR‐OLD.

20:56.423 --> 20:57.591
CAN YOU HELP ME?

20:57.624 --> 20:58.525
We sure can.

20:58.559 --> 21:01.428
What kind of basket
were you thinking of?

21:01.461 --> 21:03.030
UM...

21:03.063 --> 21:05.399
CAN YOU DELIVER
TO REN MAR TONIGHT?

21:05.432 --> 21:07.868
For an extra charge,
we sure can.

21:07.901 --> 21:10.370
GREAT. UM...

21:10.404 --> 21:11.905
WHAT HAVE YOU GOT?

21:11.939 --> 21:14.041
How about one
of our theme baskets?

21:14.074 --> 21:16.376
Casino Night,
Chocolate Universe,

21:16.410 --> 21:18.712
Gay Paree?

21:18.745 --> 21:22.149
DO YOU HAVE ANYTHING
FOR A SON

21:22.182 --> 21:27.054
WHO THINKS HIS MOTHER'S
COMPLETELY FAILED HIM?

21:27.087 --> 21:29.489
WE CAN STILL GO
TO THE RESTAURANT, YOU GUYS.

21:29.523 --> 21:31.191
IT'S FINE.

21:33.093 --> 21:35.529
DID SHE EVEN SAY
WHERE SHE WAS GOING?

21:35.562 --> 21:37.664
WHY DO YOU EVEN BOTHER
ASKING ANYMORE?

21:37.698 --> 21:39.132
WE NEVER GET
A STRAIGHT ANSWER.

21:39.166 --> 21:42.603
WE HAVE NO IDEA.
WE PROBABLY NEVER WILL.

21:42.636 --> 21:44.738
SOMETIMES I WISH
SHE'D GET ARRESTED ALREADY.

21:44.771 --> 21:46.173
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

21:46.206 --> 21:48.275
AT LEAST
WE'D KNOW WHERE SHE IS.

21:48.308 --> 21:51.178
AND, SERIOUSLY, ISN'T IT
ONLY A MATTER OF TIME?

21:51.211 --> 21:53.113
WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN MOM GETS ARRESTED?

21:53.146 --> 21:54.681
WE NEED TO MAKE A PLAN.

21:54.715 --> 21:58.252
WELL, I'M 18 NOW.
I CAN BE YOUR LEGAL GUARDIAN.

21:58.285 --> 22:00.954
WHAT ABOUT ME?
YOU CAN STILL HANG OUT.

22:00.988 --> 22:02.256
HANG OUT?!

22:02.289 --> 22:04.892
I AM THE ADULT MALE
FIGUREHEAD HERE.

22:04.925 --> 22:07.628
COME ON, ANDY.
YOU DON'T ACT LIKE AN ADULT.

22:07.661 --> 22:09.296
NONE OF US DO ‐‐
WE'RE ALL A BUNCH OF BABIES,

22:09.329 --> 22:11.532
WAITING FOR MOM
TO MAKE THE MONEY...

22:11.565 --> 22:14.234
ALWAYS LOOKING
FOR MOMMY'S APPROVAL...

22:14.268 --> 22:16.136
ASKING MOMMY'S PERMISSION.

22:16.170 --> 22:20.440
SHANE'S RIGHT.
SHE'S UNRELIABLE.

22:20.474 --> 22:21.508
SHE'S UNAVAILABLE.

22:21.542 --> 22:24.144
IT'S TIME FOR US TO TAKE ON
SOME RESPONSIBILITY,

22:24.178 --> 22:26.180
BECAUSE, FOR ALL WE KNOW,
SHE'S GOING TO PRISON.

22:26.213 --> 22:28.782
OR WORSE.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

22:28.815 --> 22:31.318
NOTHING. SHE'S FINE.

22:31.351 --> 22:35.155
I'M THINKING
OF BUYING SOME LAND IN MEXICO.

22:35.189 --> 22:38.025
REALLY? WITH WHAT?

22:38.058 --> 22:40.527
I MADE A FEW BUCKS
FROM THE CHEESE SHOP.

22:40.561 --> 22:43.931
I'M GONNA PRICE IT OUT.
NOTHING CRAZY.

22:43.964 --> 22:47.467
JUST A NICE LITTLE FARM
WHERE I CAN GROW POT,

22:47.501 --> 22:50.370
MAYBE SELL TO THE CLUBS,
A FEW CUSTOMERS.

22:50.404 --> 22:51.238
BUT THAT'S IT.

22:51.271 --> 22:55.976
NO STUPID EXPANSION.
NO STUPID MISTAKES.

22:56.009 --> 22:58.645
SMALL...

22:58.679 --> 23:00.814
MELLOW...

23:00.848 --> 23:04.084
SO I DON'T DROP DEAD OF A HEART
ATTACK BECAUSE I'M SO STRESSED

23:04.117 --> 23:07.120
FROM TRYING TO MAINTAIN
THIS BULLSHIT LIFESTYLE.

23:09.323 --> 23:12.025
I GOT A LITTLE CASH
FROM THE COYOTE GIG.

23:13.427 --> 23:15.562
YOU WANT A PARTNER?
I'LL TAKE YOUR MONEY.

23:15.596 --> 23:20.501
WHAT ABOUT ME?
YOU GO TO SCHOOL
AND BE A KID.

23:20.534 --> 23:23.470
I WANT TO HELP.
YOU CAN HELP
BY NOT TELLING MOM.

23:23.504 --> 23:26.173
THAT'S NOT A PROBLEM.
I HAVE NOTHING TO SAY TO MOM.

23:26.206 --> 23:29.176
HEY, HEY, HEY. LET'S STOP
BAGGING ON YOUR MOM, OKAY?

23:29.209 --> 23:31.278
SHE HAS DONE
SOME LESS‐THAN‐PRUDENT

23:31.311 --> 23:33.914
OR THOUGHTFUL THINGS,
BUT SHE'S NANCY.

23:33.947 --> 23:36.483
AND WE LOVE HER, ALL OF US.

23:38.485 --> 23:40.921
LOVE...

23:40.954 --> 23:42.089
HER...

23:42.122 --> 23:46.326
IN A MOM‐LOVING WAY.

23:48.262 --> 23:49.563
NOT IN ANY OTHER WAY.

23:49.596 --> 23:52.232
OF COURSE WE LOVE HER.
SHE LOVES US, TOO.

23:52.266 --> 23:54.434
BUT WHATEVER, MAN.
IT'S USELESS.

23:54.468 --> 23:57.037
I'M GETTING A POPSICLE.
ANYONE WANT?

23:57.070 --> 23:58.872
NO, THANKS.
YES.

23:58.906 --> 24:00.274
I WOULD LIKE A POPSICLE.

24:05.445 --> 24:07.181
HUH.

24:08.315 --> 24:11.084
Woman:
Security code 4‐8‐7, right?

24:11.118 --> 24:12.152
THAT'S RIGHT.

24:12.186 --> 24:14.588
Well, great.
We're all set with that.

24:14.621 --> 24:17.491
Now, what would you like
the card to say?

24:17.524 --> 24:20.360
OH, UH...

24:21.862 --> 24:23.530
"DEAR SILAS."

24:23.564 --> 24:25.132
Silas?

24:25.165 --> 24:28.268
S‐I‐L‐A‐S.
THAT'S MY SON.

24:28.302 --> 24:29.970
"DEAR SILAS."
"Dear Silas."

24:30.003 --> 24:31.104
"DEAR SILAS.

24:31.138 --> 24:33.173
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
HAPPY 18th BIRTHDAY."

24:33.207 --> 24:36.677
UM...
UH, DON'T WRITE "UM."

24:36.710 --> 24:40.747
"I THINK
YOU'RE AN AMAZING SON.

24:40.781 --> 24:46.620
I'M...SO PROUD TO...
BE YOUR MOM."

24:46.653 --> 24:48.021
"BE YOUR MOM."

24:48.055 --> 24:50.457
THAT SOUNDS LIKE BULLSHIT,
DOESN'T IT?

24:50.490 --> 24:53.460
UM...

24:53.493 --> 24:56.263
"DEAR SILAS,
IF YOU NEVER SEE ME AGAIN,

24:56.296 --> 24:57.998
"I'VE PROBABLY BEEN MURDERED.

24:58.031 --> 25:00.267
ENJOY THE DRIED APRICOTS
AND BUTTER COOKIES."

25:00.300 --> 25:01.435
Uh,
the Sterling Celebration

25:01.468 --> 25:03.003
doesn't come
with butter cookies.

25:03.036 --> 25:05.739
But if you'd like to add them,
I certainly can do that.
YEAH, UH...

25:05.772 --> 25:07.441
COULD YOU STOP TALKING
FOR A SECOND?

25:07.474 --> 25:09.977
COULD YOU JUST, UH,
PLEASE BE QUIET AND LISTEN?

25:10.010 --> 25:11.512
JUST LISTEN.

25:11.545 --> 25:13.514
I'm listening.

25:13.547 --> 25:15.549
STARTING OVER. UM...

25:17.384 --> 25:20.254
"DEAR SILAS..."

25:21.488 --> 25:23.624
UM...

25:23.657 --> 25:27.794
"THANKS FOR RAISING YOURSELF

25:27.828 --> 25:29.630
"THESE PAST 18 YEARS.

25:29.663 --> 25:32.466
"YOU'VE...

25:32.499 --> 25:34.468
DONE A GREAT JOB."

25:41.542 --> 25:43.710
Ms. Botwin?

25:45.913 --> 25:48.415
Are you okay, Ms. Botwin?

26:06.400 --> 26:10.370
"SILAS...

26:10.404 --> 26:12.372
"YOU ARE LOVED.

26:12.406 --> 26:13.373
ME."

26:13.407 --> 26:14.675
SIGN IT "ME."

26:14.708 --> 26:16.009
Just "me"?

26:16.043 --> 26:21.315
YEAH, "ME." NO, "MOM."
"ME, MOM."

26:21.348 --> 26:24.318
PLEASE ‐‐ PLEASE GET THAT
TO HIM TONIGHT.

26:24.351 --> 26:27.321
AND ‐‐ AND ADD
THE BUTTER COOKIES.

26:27.354 --> 26:30.858
YOU CAN CHARGE ME EXTRA
FOR IT, OKAY?

26:30.891 --> 26:32.860
THANKS, CAROL.

26:32.893 --> 26:34.862
You take care, Ms. Botwin.

26:34.895 --> 26:36.730
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

27:05.325 --> 27:07.961
I DON'T WANT TO BELIEVE IT.

27:07.995 --> 27:11.598
SO DON'T.

27:16.570 --> 27:19.673
I THOUGHT YOU LOVED ME.

27:19.706 --> 27:23.644
I DO LOVE YOU.

27:31.518 --> 27:38.225
YOU HAVE MADE ME SO SAD.

27:39.893 --> 27:43.397
WELL, I THINK
I CAN MAKE YOU HAPPY.

27:48.669 --> 27:50.370
IT'S TOO LATE.

27:57.344 --> 27:59.613
[ SIGHS ]

28:01.515 --> 28:03.350
[ SIGHS ]

28:17.497 --> 28:19.533
[ PICTURE SLIDES ]

28:28.709 --> 28:35.215
IT'S TOO EARLY TO TELL,
BUT IT FEELS LIKE A BOY.

